TY  - JOUR
T1  - 94%-Effective Policies for a Two-Stage Serial Inventory System with Stochastic Demand
AU  - Chen, Fangruo
Y1  - 1999/12/01
PY  - 1999
DA  - 1999/12/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.45.12.1679
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.45.12.1679
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 1679
EP  - 1696
VL  - 45
IS  - 12
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - A two-stage inventory system is considered where Poisson demand occurs at Stage 1, and Stage 1 replenishes its inventory from Stage 2, which in turn orders from an outside supplier with unlimited stock. Each shipment, either to Stage 2 or to Stage 1, incurs a fixed setup cost. Under the assumption that the supply leadtime at Stage 2 is zero, we characterize a simple heuristic policy whose long-run average cost is guaranteed to be within 6% of optimality, i.e., a 94%-effective policy. The paper also provides heuristic policies for more general inventory systems and reports computational results.
AB  - A two-stage inventory system is considered where Poisson demand occurs at Stage 1, and Stage 1 replenishes its inventory from Stage 2, which in turn orders from an outside supplier with unlimited stock. Each shipment, either to Stage 2 or to Stage 1, incurs a fixed setup cost. Under the assumption that the supply leadtime at Stage 2 is zero, we characterize a simple heuristic policy whose long-run average cost is guaranteed to be within 6% of optimality, i.e., a 94%-effective policy. The paper also provides heuristic policies for more general inventory systems and reports computational results.
